                                            p.block.block_inline
                                                strong.strong I know &lt;img&gt; what else?
                                            p HTML5 introduced &lt;figure&gt; element. This is standard for images.
                                            p MDN Example:
                                            pre.prettyprint
                                                code.code
                                                    |
                                                        &lt;figure&gt;
                                                            &lt;img src="/media/examples/elephant-660-480.jpg"
                                                                alt="Elephant at sunset"&gt;
                                                            &lt;figcaption&gt;An elephant at sunset&lt;/figcaption&gt;
                                                        &lt;/figure&gt;
                                        li.links__item
                                            p.block.block_inline
                                                strong.strong I'm confused with alternative text. W3C doesn't help. What and where should I write?
                                            p What — I've read WebAim article. They don't give abstract examples but teach you writing proper alt texts.
                                            p Where — Scott O'Hara`s article shows us the way.
                                            p Final example:
                                            pre.prettyprint
                                                code.code
                                                    |
                                                        &lt;figure role="figure" aria-label="repeat figcaption content here"&gt;
                                                            &lt;!-- figure content. if an image, provide alt text --&gt;
                                                            &lt;figcaption&gt;
                                                                Caption for the figure.
                                                            &lt;/figcaption&gt;
                                                        &lt;/figure&gt;

                                                        &lt;!--
                                                        aria-label for macOS VoiceOver + Chrome
                                                        role="figure" for IE11.

                                                        IE11 needs an accessible name (provided by aria-label).
                                                        If not for the fact VO + Chrome doesn't support an
                                                        accessible name from aria-labelledby, that attribute
                                                        would have been preferred / pointed to an ID on 
                                                        the &lt;figcaption&gt;.
                                                        --&gt;
                                        li.links__item
                                            p.block.block_inline
                                                strong.strong How to make my images print-friendly?
                                            p I use filter property. So images are black and white.
                                            p Example:
                                            pre.prettyprint
                                                code.code
                                                    |
                                                        @media print {
                                                            .figure__img {
                                                                filter: gray;
                                                                -webkit-filter: grayscale(1);
                                                                filter: grayscale(1);
                                                            }
                                                        }
